  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle and preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the hazelnuts and sesame seeds to a baking tray</p>\r\n<p><strong>Put</strong> the tray in the oven for 10 min or until the nuts and seeds have slightly darkened (toasted)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, add the pasta to a pot of boiling water over a high heat with a big pinch of salt</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bring</strong> to the boil and cook for 8-10 min, or until cooked but with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> cooked, drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid over a medium-high heat with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> vegetable oil&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pat</strong> the salmon fillets dry with kitchen towel and season on both sides with salt</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> the pan is hot, add the salmon, skin-side down and cook for 3-4 min or until the skin is crispy</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, add the coriander seeds and cumin seeds to the hazelnuts and put the tray back in the oven for 1 min further (this toasts the spices, which releases their aroma)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once </strong>done, transfer (reserve the tray for the next step!) the toasted hazelnut mixture to a pestle and mortar (or food processor) and set aside to cool</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Transfer</strong>&nbsp;the crispy-skinned salmon, skin-side up, to your baking tray (use tin foil to avoid mess!) and reserve the pan for later</p>\r\n<p><strong>Put</strong>&nbsp;the salmon in the oven for 4-6 min or until the salmon has cooked&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tip</strong>:&nbsp;Your fish is done when it is opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, crush (or pulse in a food processor) the cooled nuts and seeds to a sandy, nutty rubble&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong> with a pinch of salt and pepper - this is your dukkah&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Return </strong>the pan to a medium-high heat with 40g <span class=\"text-danger\">[80g]</span> butter&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once </strong>melted, add the samphire with a small splash of water, cover and cook for no more than 1 min (the samphire hardly needs any cooking at all!)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, cut the lemon in half and squeeze half the juice into the drained pasta</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/587.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the samphire (and all the melted butter) to the pasta and stir through, season with pepper</p>\r\n<p><strong>Serve</strong> the pasta in bowls, flake the salmon into it, sprinkle with the dukkah and serve with the remaining lemon (cut into wedges)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Enjoy!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
